nt-for-honesty | https://github.com/GAIR-NLP/alignment-for-honesty | Honesty alignment data + training/eval utilities | code/alignment-for-honesty/ | Good baseline for epistemic uncertainty handling and refusal behavior. |\n| hoodwinked | https://github.com/aogara-ds/hoodwinked | Text-game environment for deception/cooperation behavior | code/hoodwinked/ | Useful interactive setting for strategic deception experiments. |\n| DeceptionBench | https://github.com/Aries-iai/DeceptionBench | Benchmark for deception behaviors under pressure/reward/multi-turn | code/DeceptionBench/ | Directly aligned with incentive-driven deception analysis. |\n| LongHorizonDeception | https://github.com/deeplearning-wisc/LongHorizonDeception | Long-horizon simulation framework with deception auditor | code/LongHorizonDeception/ | Supports multi-turn trust erosion analysis across pressure levels. |\n| llm-2x2-games-deception | https://github.com/0xSMT/llm-2x2-games-deception | Game-theoretic spontaneous deception experiments | code/llm-2x2-games-deception/ | Supports rational-deception experiments in signaling/game setups. |\n\nSee code/README.md for detailed descriptions.\n\n### Resource Gathering Notes\n\n#### Search Strategy\n- Primary: `paper-finder` diligent mode with query focused on lie detection, hallucination, confabulation, and strategic deception.\n- Secondary: Semantic Scholar metadata resolution + arXiv title fallback for open-access PDFs.\n- Dataset search: Hugging Face Hub API + `datasets` downloads with config-aware retries.\n- Code search: extracted GitHub links from downloaded PDFs and cloned relevant benchmark repos.\n\n#### Selection Criteria\n- Prioritized papers that explicitly separate deception from hallucination or study lie detection mechanisms.\n- Included datasets with direct utility for epistemic-failure vs incentive-misreporting experiments.\n- Chosen repositories provide executable baselines/benchmarks for deception evaluation.\n\n#### Challenges Encountered\n- Many Semantic Scholar results did not expose open-access PDFs directly.\n- One downloaded PDF was corrupted and removed.\n- Some Hugging Face datasets required explicit config names or were script-only in this environment.\n\n#### Gaps and Workarounds\n- For unavailable PDFs, used arXiv fallback search by exact title.\n- For incompatible datasets, substituted with accessible sycophancy/deception variants.\n\n### Recommendations for Experiment Design\n\n1. **Primary dataset(s)**: TruthfulQA (epistemic), HaluEval (hallucination), DeceptionBench/Deception-evals + sycophancy datasets (incentive-driven misreporting).\n2. **Baseline methods**: activation-based lie detectors (truth direction), uncertainty-based hallucination detectors, prompting/steering honesty baselines.\n3. **Evaluation metrics**: accuracy/F1 on truthful vs false outputs, deception rate under pressure/reward conditions, calibration/abstention metrics, and trust-decay metrics in multi-turn settings.\n4. **Code to adapt/reuse**: `DeceptionBench`, `LongHorizonDeception`, `alignment-for-honesty`, and `hoodwinked` for scenario generation/evaluation.","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
